\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 MicroEMACS is a very powerful tool to use for editing text files. It has many {\ul commands}{\v Command}, options and features to let you do j
ust about anything you can imagine with text. But don't let this apparent complexity keep you from using it.... MicroEMACS can also be very simple.
\par \pard \s6\sa120 To start editing text, all the keys you really need to know are the arrow keys. These keys let you move around in your file.
\par MicroEMACS also works by using control keys. Here are a few basic commands:
\par \pard\plain \s14\fi-900\li900\tqr\tx720\tx900 \f2\fs20\lang1033 \tab {\ul ^P}{\v Keystroke}\tab Move upward
\par \tab {\ul ^B}{\v Keystroke}\tab Move backward
\par \tab {\ul ^F}{\v Keystroke}\tab Move forward
\par \tab {\ul ^N}{\v Keystroke}\tab Move downward
\par \tab {\ul ^X^S}{\v Keystroke}\tab Save your file
\par \pard \s14\fi-900\li900\sa120\tqr\tx720\tx900 \tab {\ul ^X^C}{\v Keystroke}\tab Exit MicroEMACS
\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 A hat sign "{\b ^}" before a key means to hold the Ctrl key down and press the next character. For example, to exit MicroEMACS, hold down the Ctrl key and strike X and then C.
