\par \pard\plain \s4\fi-2160\li2880\sa120\tx2880 \f27\fs18\lang1033 bind-to-key   meta-prefix   ~
\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 You can use this to make MicroEMACS feel similar to another editor by changing what keys activate which commands. 
\par \pard \s6\sa120 The {\uldb unbind-key}{\v unbind_key} command is useful if you have a function key you keep tripping over, or if you are trying to make MicroEMACS look like a much more minimalist editor. 
